First used 1996 (this needs to be checked).

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# A [[virtual]] [[sexual]] [[encounter]] in which two or more persons [[connected]] [[remotely]] via a computer network send one another sexually [[explicit]] [[messages]] describing a sexual experience.
#: ''He went to his office and logged online to have '''cybersex''' for more than six hours.'' In the shadows of the net: 2001. Hazelden Foundation P65.


===Verb===
'''cybersex'''

# To exchange explicit sexual experiences online via text or [[multimedia]].
# To engage in sexual activity, usually [[masturbation]], while communincating [[online]] with another person.


